            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
                <p>This graffito belongs to the category of ownership inscriptions that are sometimes identified as 'speaking objects.' 
                    Σμικης must therefore be a genetive form, either of the feminine name Σμίκα or of the male name Σμίκηος.
                    <!--(see Dubois, Vinogradov, and Tokhtasiev)
                    or feminine name Σμικη?  ... The name is attested.... Information on the context of find is taken from the inventory card.
                    Inventory card (Krasotkina, Bilimovich under the supervision of Tolstoy, 1948) gives the reading Σμίκης εἰμί. 
                    They translate: "Принадлежу Смике," presumably taking the name to be feminine. --></p>
                <p><!--Received from the Archaeological Commission in 1904.--></p>  
            </div>
